  <front>
    <title>OAuth 2.0 Authorization Server Issuer Identification</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-ietf-oauth-iss-auth-resp-01"/>
    <author initials="K. M." surname="zu Selhausen" fullname="Karsten Meyer zu Selhausen">
      <organization>Hackmanit</organization>
    </author>
    <author initials="D." surname="Fett" fullname="Daniel Fett">
      <organization>yes.com</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="08" month="June" year="2021"></date>
    <abstract>
      <t>   This document specifies a new parameter "iss" that is used to
   explicitly include the issuer identifier of the authorization server
   in the authorization response of an OAuth authorization flow.  The
   "iss" parameter serves as an effective countermeasure to "mix-up
   attacks".

	 </t>
    </abstract>
